The paper discusses a novel framework for semi-supervised learning using deep generative models, specifically Variational Autoencoder (VAE) and Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN). These models are commonly used in the fields of machine learning and computer vision, which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI. The paper also evaluates the proposed approach on real-world applications, which suggests relevance to the sub-categories cs.CL (natural language processing) and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing).
